lity activities based on the global Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) Group Corporate Social Responsibility Policy and Strategy. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) specifies detailed requirements towards its suppliers in the document ` Business Partner’s Code of Conduct´. The whole set of documents is available on Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA)’s homepage, section `Suppliers - Purchasing Documents`. To improve transparency on sustainability on our supply chain, eligible suppliers identified by Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) must provide the necessary information during onboarding or evaluation processes, which may include answering sustainability questionnaires or similar assessments when requested. Suppliers are required to cooperate and share relevant details upon request. 3.5 Product  Safety Product  safety and product liability are particularly significant for companies in the automotive industry. The supplier has producer responsibility (product liability) for their parts and processes, including parts or processes from sub-suppliers, which Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) purchases to build their final products. Therefore, in order to prevent product liability risks, it is the responsibility of the supplier to do everything in their power, in terms of organization and technical matters, to guarantee the product safety. The supplier shall have a documented process for the management of “product safety” related products and manufacturing processes. Yazaki (Yazaki EMEA) requires their suppliers to designate a Product  Safety Representative (PSCR (Product Safety & Conformity Representative)) to be in charge of all related tasks described"
}


